{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Image\/fixedSize()","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"nonisolated"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"fixedSize"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"some"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"View","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View"},{"kind":"text","text":"\n"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"text":"Return Value","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"return-value"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A view that fixes this view at its ideal size.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"},{"content":[{"text":"Discussion","level":2,"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"During the layout of the view hierarchy, each view proposes a size to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"each child view it contains. If the child view doesn’t need a fixed size","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"it can accept and conform to the size offered by the parent.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For example, a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Text"},{"type":"text","text":" view placed in an explicitly sized frame wraps"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and truncates its string to remain within its parent’s bounds:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["Text(\"A single line of text, too long to fit in a box.\")","    .frame(width: 200, height: 200)","    .border(Color.gray)"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fixedSize()"},{"type":"text","text":" modifier can be used to create a view that maintains"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"ideal size"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" of its children both dimensions:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["Text(\"A single line of text, too long to fit in a box.\")","    .fixedSize()","    .frame(width: 200, height: 200)","    .border(Color.gray)"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This can result in the view exceeding the parent’s bounds, which may or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"may not be the effect you want."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You can think of ","type":"text"},{"code":"fixedSize()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" as the creation of a ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"counter proposal","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to the view size proposed to a view by its parent. The ideal size of a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"view, and the specific effects of ","type":"text"},{"code":"fixedSize()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" depends on the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"particular view and how you have configured it.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"To create a view that fixes the view’s size in either the horizontal or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"vertical dimensions, see ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View\/fixedSize(horizontal:vertical:)","type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"metadata":{"extendedModule":"OpenSwiftUICore","platforms":[{"name":"iOS","deprecated":false,"beta":false,"introducedAt":"1